Store Cards app to help you transfer all your loyalty cards to your smartphone.

Use cards when you need them: get discounts, pay for purchases with your smartphone using the Store Cards service, save and spend bonuses.

How does Store Cards work?
- Choose a loyalty card from the list of preset cards;
- Open the barcode on your device;
- Show the barcode to the cashier;
- Get your points, bonuses, rewards.

What are card templates?
The templates contain web addresses, links to detailed information about loyalty programs, promotions, discounts and offers, vouchers, coupons, bonus and gift cards.

The template database includes the most popular maps in Australia, Belarus, Canada, France, Georgia, Germany, Ireland, Italy, Russia, South Africa, Spain, UK, Ukraine and the USA.

Store Card saves your battery.
The app only consumes battery when you are using it, no power-consuming operations are performed in the background.

The Store Cards respects your privacy and requires only minimal permissions to run.

Key features of the app:
- Does not require registration or subscription;
- Work in offline mode;
- Support for Apple Watch;
- Support Apple Wallet;
- iCloud Backup & Restore;
- Protection of your data with a password;
- Export and import via Wi-Fi network;
- Local and remote export and import of card documents;
- Customize the interface to your taste;
- Support for dark mode;
- Support for the "Today" widget;
- Search for your cards and templates using voice commands and shortcuts;
- Automatic correction of card photos in accordance with the borders of the frame;
- Optical recognition of cards and much more;
- Full help with detailed instructions.

Supported barcode formats and main uses:
- Code 39, Code 93 and Code 128: Name Badges, Inventory and Industrial Applications;
- EAN 8 and EAN 13: identification of a specific type of retail product in a specific packaging configuration from a specific manufacturer;
- Aztec: sale of transport tickets, especially on trains, planes and ferries;
- Data Matrix: labeling of small items such as computer components and packaging;
- PDF417: many applications such as transportation, ID cards and inventory management;
- UPC A and UPC E: identification of product characteristics such as brand name, product, size and color;
- QR Code: Storing data in a wide variety of scenarios such as plain text messages, addresses, phone numbers, email addresses, URLs, app links, payments, online account authentication, and WiFi authentication.

Some features of the app are limited by default.  For example, you can enter 15 loyalty cards for free: eight main cards and seven cards for watching prize videos.
What does a PRO subscription give?  Unlimited virtual wallets, Apple Wallet support, no ads in the app.

Our team made a Store Card application so that you can save time searching for cards in your wallet, bag, backpack.  At the same time, we have made a beautiful, simple design so that you get a sleek and convenient mobile application with an intuitive interface.

